comments.message:
This seems relatively easy to compute with:

```
std::count_if(ipv4Data.begin(), ipv4Data.end(), [](const IPv4AddressData& addr){
    return addr.origin == "Static";
});
```

Everything else in this struct is coming directly from dbus, and isn't a computed value.  I'd like to keep that abstraction if possible.  Would the above code let us just compute the value when we needed it?

Do we need to set gatewayValue in this path?  If there's already an ip address with a gateway, we want to count it, right?

Something like
```
gatewayValue = nicIpEntry->gateway;
activePath = pathString;
gatewayValueAssigned = true;
```
?

I'm imagining the case where we have one ip address set, then we do
```
PATCH: [
{}.
{Gateway: Gateway that doesn't match 0}
]
```

I think we would incorrectly set the gateway of the second one, right?
